```java
public class PowerOfThree {

    public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }

        return n == 1;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(27)); // true
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(0)); // false
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(-1)); // false
    }
}
```

This solution uses a while loop to repeatedly divide the input number by 3 until it is equal to 1. If the input number is ever divisible by 3, then it must be a power of three. Otherwise, it is not a power of three.

